# able.word — what a ABLE is, a composite word. Descends from word.word, can.word, being.word,
# space.word, and the verbs. The host registry is seed/present/ables/registry.js. A able composes
# from words already grounded, no new primitive. Its can is the granted words grouped by verb
# (canSee, canDo collapse into the verbs). Its voice is the prompt, worn not granted. Its scope is
# the space it is given on, and all under it. flow, when a being may play a able, comes next.

A able is a composite word, a can of words.
A able has a name, its handle.
A able's can is words to see, do, call, be, and recall, each word for its verb.
A able has a voice, the manner a being takes in it, no word it can.
A able has a space, and its words can there and under it, its scope. A able may set its scope to more paths, or less, by path.
A name grants a able to a being, all of it, at a space or a being.
Ables stack. A being with many has the words of all.
Through a being granted a able, a Name acts by its words within the able's space, and the being has it as it moves.
